Implement an automated test framework that validates that each protocol defined in the Protocol Finder 2.0 library is correctly selected when appropriate patient input data is provided.

The objective of this system is to simulate real patient profiles and verify that the correct protocol is selected according to clinical logic, priority rules, and protocol routing hierarchy.

The system must automatically test every protocol defined in the normalized protocol library and confirm that:

Each protocol can be triggered.
Each protocol appears when correct clinical conditions are entered.
Each protocol is not incorrectly skipped.
Each protocol contains valid compounds.
Each protocol produces valid timelines.

